This paper deals with the problem of visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach for constructing a target appearance model using discriminatively learned correlation filters, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which involves performance evaluation of computer vision algorithms, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an optimization strategy for efficient online learning, which involves optimization techniques, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
